EXTRA NOTES:
These currently supported versions of SWOS have been tested on 68o3o
and 68o6o and now operate as they should.

45 Seperate saves are still allowed.

KNOWN BUGS:
SWOS still has one bug in the game which is present in the original.

If you want to view a HIGHLIGHT, you MUST have already loaded a game and
played!  It does not matter if you only play on the pitch for 2 seconds or
2 hours, the HIGHLIGHTS option expects you to have already loaded a game,
otherwise it will hang.

For purists of SWOS, you know this already ;)



Signed Galahad of Fairlight

NOTE FROM MAINTAINER:

 Version 2.0 has been adapted to use fastmem to overcome the most annoying
 slowdown bug on accelerated amigas. I didn't take the time to test all features
 (load/save) on all versions. That should work exactly as before. Please report bugs
 when found and specify your version if you can / attach the "SWOS2" file

 Version 2.2 has been improved by removing the complex (and probably cornercase buggy)
 Galahad cached dir version. Now teams can be edited, saved, and loaded back.
 While testing, I noticed a random bug. Game tends to crash with access fault when
 selecting a team. It's not that frequent, but it happens. I've tried to limit the impact
 of the bug, but if you see that the game is not behaving properly, just quit and restart.
 
 On this version, all user data (career, diy, tactics, ...) is saved in "SAVE" directory.
 When loading a tactic, other file types are shown (same as when operating from floppy).
 Just ignore them.
 
 This version also allows to load bigger uncompressed teams files without having to RNC-pack them. It
 doesn't remove the uncompressed size team limitation, though.
 
JOTD


 